<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1329,266,332]" box="[151,290,266,291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis box="[151,290,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1329,266,332]" box="[198,1329,306,332]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
ɗ, length (from apex of vertex to tip of fore wings) 
<quantity box="[803,947,306,332]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.55" metricValueMax="7.2" metricValueMin="5.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="6.55" valueMax="7.2" valueMin="5.9">5.9–7.2 mm</quantity>
; fore wings length: 
<quantity box="[1180,1325,306,332]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.199999999999999" metricValueMax="5.6" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="5.199999999999999" valueMax="5.6" valueMin="4.8">4.8–5.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175878/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" targetBox="[217,1357,403,1662]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1693,1755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,350,1693,1717]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">FIGURES 12–16.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[357,516,1693,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Tropiduchidae" genus="Zema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[357,516,1693,1716]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Zema montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[524,606,1693,1716]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
12. head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 13. head, ventral view; 14. head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 15. right fore wing; 16. right hind wing.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1810,2036]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,152,258]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">General color brown; two patches on disc of vertex and a narrow, longitudinal stripe beyond median carina on pronotum blackish; frontal disc and clypeus largely fuscous; a broad band overlying fronto-clypeal suture ivory-white; clypeus with two, longitudinal piceous stripes beyond median carina; tip of rostrum fuscous; eyes reddish; most of gena ivory-white, with a blackish patch between eye and lateral margin of vertex and a large circular, black patch below eye; antennae with pedicel black, sensory plaque organs white; pronotum with ventral portion of lateral lobes covered with an oblique, blackish stripe, and the marginal portion ivory-white; mesonotum with irregular, blackish stripes, base of mesoscutellum with fuscous suffusion; legs covered with longitudinal, fuscous stripes on femora, tibiae, pro- and mesotarsi; abdominal sclerites blackish; fore wings transparent, veins brown, apex of clavus with blackish suffusion.</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175879/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" targetBox="[188,1387,316,1974]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1975,2033]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,349,1975,1999]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">FIGURES 17–21.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[355,514,1976,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Tropiduchidae" genus="Zema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[355,514,1976,1999]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicName box="[355,414,1976,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Tropiduchidae" genus="Zema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Zema</taxonomicName>
montana
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[521,603,1975,1998]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
17. male genitalia, lateral view; 18. male genitalia, dorsal view; 19. male genitalia, caudal view; 20. anal segment and aedeagus, lateral view; 21. corpus connective and parameres, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,152,418]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[292,378,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1693,1717]" captionTargetBox="[217,1357,403,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1394,381,1687]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 16. Zema montana sp. nov. 12. head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 13. head, ventral view; 14. head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 15. right fore wing; 16. right hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175878/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
Fig. 
<number box="[348,378,152,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) distinctly shorter in midline line than breadth at base (
<number box="[1041,1104,152,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" value="2.14">2.14</number>
: 
<number box="[1109,1120,152,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" value="1.0">1</number>
). Frons (
<figureCitation box="[1226,1312,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1693,1717]" captionTargetBox="[217,1357,403,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1394,381,1687]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 16. Zema montana sp. nov. 12. head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 13. head, ventral view; 14. head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 15. right fore wing; 16. right hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175878/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
Fig. 
<number box="[1282,1312,152,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) longer in middle than the widest breadth (
<number box="[545,606,192,218]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" value="1.44">1.44</number>
: 
<number box="[610,621,192,218]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" value="1.0">1</number>
), with a broad callus at anterior margin, longitudinal carina, which between middle line and lateral carina, nearly parallel, uniting with median carina in the broad callus. Clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[159,300,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1693,1717]" captionTargetBox="[217,1357,403,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1394,381,1687]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 16. Zema montana sp. nov. 12. head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 13. head, ventral view; 14. head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 15. right fore wing; 16. right hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175878/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Figs. 13, 14</figureCitation>
) with thicken median carina.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,152,418]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[382,522,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox="[188,1387,316,1974]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,314,1977]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 21. Zema montana sp. nov. 17. male genitalia, lateral view; 18. male genitalia, dorsal view; 19. male genitalia, caudal view; 20. anal segment and aedeagus, lateral view; 21. corpus connective and parameres, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175879/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
Figs. 
<number box="[448,522,312,338]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" value="19.0" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="17.0">17–21</number>
</figureCitation>
) relatively large, Periandrium (
<figureCitation box="[888,1072,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox="[188,1387,316,1974]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,314,1977]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 21. Zema montana sp. nov. 17. male genitalia, lateral view; 18. male genitalia, dorsal view; 19. male genitalia, caudal view; 20. anal segment and aedeagus, lateral view; 21. corpus connective and parameres, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175879/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
Figs. 17, 18, 
<number box="[1041,1072,312,338]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
) large and elongate, symmetrical, with its basal half surrounding basal 
<number box="[627,637,352,378]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[648,664,352,378]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" value="2.0">2</number>
of penis; penis slender and elongate, distinctly sinuate, apical half directed posteroventrally in lateral view, apex distinctly forked.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
